"No parent should have to bury a child... No mother should have to bury a son. Mothers are not meant to bury sons. It is not in the natural order of things."

I personally do not know what it feels like to lose someone. I hope I do not live long enough to know what that is like. The twins & Cam are truly admirable for being strong at a young age. I do hope they all get the chance to mourn/grieve Sean's passing in the confines of their whole family's presence alone--no cameras, no phones.

snippet.textDisplay: My grandma died from cancer in 2018 and I’m still not over it. When she passed away all I would do is cry. I have to be there for my mom and my granddad.  The last time I saw her she just smiled and she looked so happy but she knew she was gonna die soon. The night she died I had friends over,I was getting a drink and I saw my mom rush out of her room crying getting ready. I asked her what was wrong and she told me the news. I couldn’t comprehend it so I just froze and broke down. My sister and friends came in there and saw us and my sister was looked broken. My friends were just shocked. After that happened I went to school and I just felt broken and I just wanted to sleep and cry. I had no therapy nor did I have friends to help. My teachers understood what happened but when I went back to school after what happened after I had a break I still had breakdowns in class and I just couldn’t listen to anything. I felt like nothing was real and I was just gonna wake up and everyone be happy and healthy but that’s not how life works. I still cry and remember that I could have been there for her more but I didn’t. If anyone is reading this and has made it to this point I want you to know they wouldn’t want you to cry over their death. They would want you to you to live your life and be happy. I’m not good at expressing my emotions but I can help people from experience. Remember I love you and your valid. I’m so proud that you have made it this far and I want you to keep going for them. I have to be there for my mom and my granddad.  The last time I saw her she just smiled and she looked so happy but she knew she was gonna die soon. The night she died I had friends over,I was getting a drink and I saw my mom rush out of her room crying getting ready. I asked her what was wrong and she told me the news. I couldn’t comprehend it so I just froze and broke down. My sister and friends came in there and saw us and my sister was looked broken. My friends were just shocked. After that happened I went to school and I just felt broken and I just wanted to sleep and cry. I had no therapy nor did I have friends to help. My teachers understood what happened but when I went back to school after what happened after I had a break I still had breakdowns in class and I just couldn’t listen to anything. I felt like nothing was real and I was just gonna wake up and everyone be happy and healthy but that’s not how life works. I still cry and remember that I could have been there for her more but I didn’t. If anyone is reading this and has made it to this point I want you to know they wouldn’t want you to cry over their death. They would want you to you to live your life and be happy. I’m not good at expressing my emotions but I can help people from experience. Remember I love you and your valid. I’m so proud that you have made it this far and I want you to keep going for them. I love you :)
